---
/**
 * FeaturesZigzag - Alternating left/right feature blocks
 * Each feature has text + code snippet or illustration
 */
---

<section class="features-section not-content">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Built for the Quantum Era</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">What makes QPKI different.</p>

    <!-- Feature 1: Post-Quantum Ready -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge">Core</span>
        <h3>Post-Quantum Ready</h3>
        <p>PQC via Cloudflare CIRCL. ML-DSA for signatures, ML-KEM for key encapsulation, SLH-DSA for hash-based signatures. PQ & hybrid certificates cross-tested with OpenSSL and BouncyCastle.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/getting-started/post-quantum/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Generate ML-DSA key pair</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki key generate \
    --algorithm <span class="h">ml-dsa-65</span> \
    --out root-ca.key
<span class="o">&#10003; ML-DSA-65 key pair generated</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 2: Hybrid Certificates (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge blue">Migration</span>
        <h3>Hybrid Certificates</h3>
        <p>Dual-algorithm certificates combine classical with post-quantum algorithms. Backward compatible with existing infrastructure while quantum-safe.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/migration/hybrid/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Generate hybrid CSR (Catalyst mode)</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki csr gen \
    --algorithm <span class="h">ecdsa-p256</span> \
    --hybrid <span class="h">ml-dsa-65</span> \
    --cn "api.example.com"
<span class="o">&#10003; Hybrid CSR generated</span>

<span class="c"># Issue from hybrid CSR</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cert issue \
    --profile <span class="h">hybrid/catalyst/tls-server</span> \
    --csr hybrid.csr
<span class="o">&#10003; Hybrid certificate issued</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 3: Crypto-Agile -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge green">Agility</span>
        <h3>Crypto-Agile by Design</h3>
        <p>Each credential bundles multiple certificates — classical and post-quantum — with a coupled lifecycle. Enroll today, rotate to new algorithms tomorrow. Declarative profiles make migration a one-line operation.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/migration/crypto-agility/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Enroll with classical crypto</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki credential enroll <span class="h">api-server</span> \
    --profile <span class="h">ec/tls-server</span> ...
<span class="o">&#10003; Credential enrolled · ECDSA-P256</span>

<span class="c"># Rotate to post-quantum</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki credential rotate <span class="h">api-server</span> \
    --profile <span class="h">ml/tls-server</span>
<span class="o">&#10003; Rotated to ML-DSA-65</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 4: HSM Support (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge purple">Enterprise</span>
        <h3>HSM Ready</h3>
        <p>PKCS#11 integration for hardware security modules. Keep private keys in tamper-resistant hardware. Works with air-gapped and FIPS-validated environments.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/operations/hsm/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Initialize CA with HSM-backed keys</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki ca init \
    --profile ml/root-ca \
    --hsm-config <span class="h">hsm.yaml</span> \
    --key-label "pq-root-ca"
<span class="o">&#10003; Root CA created · key stored in HSM</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 5: Document Signing -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge indigo">Signature</span>
        <h3>Document Signing</h3>
        <p>CMS signatures with ML-DSA produce detached <code>.p7s</code> proofs that travel alongside any file — contracts, invoices, firmware. Classical signatures can be forged retroactively once quantum computers arrive; ML-DSA signatures remain unforgeable. Verify in one command, no proprietary tooling required.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/services/cms/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Sign document with ML-DSA</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cms sign \
    --data <span class="h">contract.pdf</span> \
    --credential signer \
    --out contract.p7s
<span class="o">&#10003; Signed with ML-DSA-65 (detached)</span>

<span class="c"># Verify signature</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cms verify contract.p7s \
    --data contract.pdf --ca ca.crt
<span class="o">&#10003; Valid · ML-DSA-65</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 6: CMS Encryption (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge orange">Encryption</span>
        <h3>Data Encryption</h3>
        <p>CMS encryption with ML-KEM key encapsulation. Defeat harvest-now-decrypt-later: data intercepted today stays protected even when quantum computers arrive. RFC 9880 (ML-KEM in CMS) and RFC 9883 attestation for KEM enrollment.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/services/cms/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Encrypt document with ML-KEM</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cms encrypt \
    --recipient <span class="h">alice-ml-kem.crt</span> \
    --in report.pdf \
    --out report.pdf.p7m
<span class="o">&#10003; Encrypted with ML-KEM-768</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 7: PQC Timestamping -->
    <div class="feature-row fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge cyan">Long-Term</span>
        <h3>Quantum-Proof Timestamps</h3>
        <p>RFC 3161 timestamping with ML-DSA. Classical timestamps can be forged once quantum computers break their signatures — PQC timestamps remain unforgeable against quantum attacks. Built-in HTTP server for production deployment.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/services/tsa/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Timestamp a document with ML-DSA</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki tsa sign \
    --data <span class="h">contract.pdf</span> \
    --credential tsa \
    --out contract.tsr
<span class="o">&#10003; Timestamped with ML-DSA-65</span>

<span class="c"># Verify timestamp</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki tsa verify --token contract.tsr \
    --data contract.pdf --ca ca.crt
<span class="o">&#10003; Valid · 2026-03-17T14:30:00Z</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 8: Post-Quantum Authentication (reversed) -->
    <div class="feature-row reversed fade-in">
      <div class="feature-text">
        <span class="feature-badge yellow">IAM</span>
        <h3>Secure Tokens</h3>
        <p>CWT tokens signed with ML-DSA replace vulnerable JWT/JWS for identity, access control, and device attestation. Protect claims and audit trails against retroactive quantum forgery. Hybrid mode ensures backward compatibility with existing COSE infrastructure.</p>
        <a href="/qpki/services/cose/" class="feature-link">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-code">
        <div class="mini-terminal">
          <div class="mini-header" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span><span class="dot-sm"></span></div>
          <pre><code><span class="c"># Issue PQ auth token (CWT)</span>
<span class="p">$</span> qpki cose sign \
    --cert <span class="h">auth-server.crt</span> \
    --key auth-server.key \
    --iss "https://auth.example.com" \
    --sub "user@example.com" \
    --exp 1h \
    -o <span class="h">auth-token.cbor</span>
<span class="o">&#10003; CWT signed with ML-DSA-65</span></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features-section {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-title {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 550px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
  }

  .feature-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .feature-row:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .feature-row.reversed {
    direction: rtl;
  }

  .feature-row.reversed > * {
    direction: ltr;
  }

  .feature-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: rgba(255, 85, 163, 0.1);
    color: #FF55A3;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 85, 163, 0.2);
  }

  .feature-badge.blue {
    background: rgba(0, 91, 197, 0.1);
    color: #60a5fa;
    border-color: rgba(0, 91, 197, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.green {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
    color: #22c55e;
    border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.purple {
    background: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.1);
    color: #a855f7;
    border-color: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.orange {
    background: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.1);
    color: #f97316;
    border-color: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.cyan {
    background: rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.1);
    color: #06b6d4;
    border-color: rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.yellow {
    background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.1);
    color: #eab308;
    border-color: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-badge.indigo {
    background: rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.1);
    color: #818cf8;
    border-color: rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.25);
  }

  .feature-text h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--sl-color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .feature-text p {
    color: var(--sl-color-gray-3);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .feature-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #FF55A3;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .feature-link:hover {
    color: #ff79b8;
  }

  /* Mini terminal */
  .mini-terminal {
    background: var(--q-terminal-bg);
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .mini-header {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  .dot-sm {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  .mini-terminal pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .mini-terminal code {
    font-family: var(--q-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #e2e8f0;
    background: none !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
  }

  .mini-terminal .c { color: #64748b; }
  .mini-terminal .p { color: #FF55A3; }
  .mini-terminal .h { color: #FF55A3; font-weight: 600; }
  .mini-terminal .o { color: #22c55e; }

  /* Light mode */
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal {
    background: var(--q-terminal-bg-light);
    border-color: #e2e8f0;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-header {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    border-bottom-color: #e2e8f0;
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal code {
    color: #1e293b;
  }

  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .c { color: #94a3b8; }
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .p { color: #005BC5; }
  :root[data-theme='light'] .mini-terminal .h { color: #005BC5; }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .feature-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .feature-row.reversed {
      direction: ltr;
    }

    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
